cs.IT, cs.DM, cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the universality and reprogramming capabilities of computer programs and compilers, which are topics that are likely to fall under the categories of information theory (cs.IT), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), logic in computer science (cs.LO), computational complexity (cs.CC), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper's focus on the complexity, controllability, causality, and (re)programmability of computer programs and compilers suggests that it is likely to be relevant to these sub-categories.
